research_municipality_step.notes: Livingston, TX operates under a manager-council system of government, which is a variation of the mayor-council type. The Mayor and Council Members were confirmed through recent election results and the official city website. The city council members are also referred to as Aldermen/Alderpersons. Divisions (wards/districts) are not specified for individual council members in the available information, though the city council is made up of members elected from single-member districts, and some council members are elected at-large.
